<p>From the documentation <a href="http://php.net/manual/en/pdostatement.fetchall.php" rel="nofollow">fetchAll</a> and <a href="http://php.net/manual/en/pdostatement.setfetchmode.php" rel="nofollow">FETCH_CLASS</a> : </p>  <pre><code>&lt;?php class fruit {     public $name;     public $colour; }  $sth = $dbh-&gt;prepare("SELECT name, colour FROM fruit"); $sth-&gt;execute();  $result = $sth-&gt;fetchAll(PDO::FETCH_CLASS, "fruit"); var_dump($result); ?&gt; </code></pre>  <p>It often happens that columns names are different from the fields defined in the classes. I'm wondering if there is some clean way to get the fields of the class populated when the query fetches different columns names : </p>  <pre><code>$sth = $dbh-&gt;prepare("SELECT f_name, f_colour FROM fruit"); </code></pre>  <p>Is there a generic solution to map columns name to fiels ? I tried several combinations for the FETCH_MODE, hoping one of them would pass the results into the constructor, but none of them worked. </p>